<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="14" pageNumber="451">
Elytra long, ca. 2.9 times longer than wide at humeri, almost parallel-sided; with four equally developed primary costae, not much different from secondary ones; interstices with irregular rows of small roundish cells; pubescence dense, short and decumbent, almost completely obscuring reticulation (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1104,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–33" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[174,1415,392,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-120@11.[159,1429,380,1914]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28–33. General view of Platerodrilus, males: 28–29— P. (Duliticola) svetae; 30—P. (D.) strbai; 31—P. (D.) berastagiensis sp. nov.; 32—P. (Zhelongia) grootaerti; 33—P. (Zh.) holynskae; 30–31, 33—holotypes; 28–29, 32—paratypes. Scale bars: 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4752683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4752683/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="451">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,789]" box="[199,1083,259,285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="451">
