<figureCitation box="[986,1069,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–33" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[174,1415,392,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-120@11.[159,1429,380,1914]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 28–33. General view of Platerodrilus, males: 28–29— P. (Duliticola) svetae; 30—P. (D.) strbai; 31—P. (D.) berastagiensis sp. nov.; 32—P. (Zhelongia) grootaerti; 33—P. (Zh.) holynskae; 30–31, 33—holotypes; 28–29, 32—paratypes. Scale bars: 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4752683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4752683/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="451">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="14" pageNumber="451">
Abdominal terminalia relatively broad; penultimate tergite medially narrowed, with median triangular incision distally and proximally; terminal ventrite moderately long, its distal portion attenuate (
<figureCitation box="[1121,1202,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–42" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[172,1423,413,1872]" captionTargetId="figure-98@13.[151,1436,381,1885]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 34–42. Details of Platerodrilus, males: 34–35—P. (s. str.) gorbunovi sp. nov.; 36—P. (s. str.) kambanganus sp. nov.; 37–38—P. (Duliticola) svetae; 39—P. (D.) strbai; 40—P. (D.) berastagiensis sp. nov.; 41—P. (Zhelongia) grootaerti; 42—P. (Zh.) holynskae; 34–36, 38–40, 42—holotypes; 37, 41—paratypes; 37, 41—hind wing; 34–36, 38–40, 42—terminal abdominal segments; 34, 36, 38–40,—dorsal view; 35, 37, 41—ventral view; 42—lateral view. Scale bars: 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4752685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4752685/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="451">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="14" pageNumber="451">
Male genitalia with transverse, rectangularly proximally incised phallobase; median lobe narrow, relatively short and evenly curved in lateral view, slightly widened distally and conspicuously widened proximally; parameres completely sclerotised, constituting ca. 0.7 length of median lobe, evenly curved in lateral aspect, with numerous sharp dents on outer ventral surface, median diamond-shaped incision proximally at base dorsally and a pair of husk-like, noticeably curved proximal apodemes (
<figureCitation box="[711,842,510,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–59" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1925,1949]" captionTargetBox="[163,1420,424,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-59@15.[151,1436,412,1902]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 49–59. Aedeagi of Platerodrilus, males: 49–50—P. (Duliticola) svetae; 51–52—P. (D.) strbai; 53–55—P. (D.) berastagiensis sp. nov.; 56–57—P. (Zhelongia) grootaerti; 58–59—P. (Zh.) holynskae; 49–55, 58–59—holotypes; 56–57—paratype; 55—dorsal view; 49, 51, 53, 56, 58—ventral view; 50, 52, 54, 57, 59—lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4752693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4752693/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="451">Figs 53–55</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,789]" box="[199,683,547,573]" pageId="14" pageNumber="451">Length: 9.7 mm. Width at humeri: 2.4 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,789]" box="[199,418,583,609]" pageId="14" pageNumber="451">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,583,609]" pageId="14" pageNumber="451">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
